<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="leave-v">leave <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /liːv/    美 /liːv/  </p>
<p>(left, left)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>离开；出发：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We were leaving very early so we packed the night before. 
我们要很早出发，所以前一天晚上我们就收拾好了行李。</p><footer>2013 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You will be able to leave the exam room when you have finished. 
答完卷后你就可以离开考场。</p><footer>外研④ – 7</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She will <strong>leave</strong> (Beijing) <strong>for</strong> Hongkong on business very soon. 
她很快就要(离开北京)去香港出差。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>使处于 (某种状态)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>leave sb / sth doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should not leave the tap water running or waste any materials in the laboratory class. 
在实验课上，我们不应该忘记关水龙头或者浪费材料。</p><footer>2007 福建</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>leave … + done / adj / adv:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I left the door unlocked when I went out. 
我出去时没锁门。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Running a marathon will leave you breathless.  
跑一场马拉松会让你上气不接下气。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Leave the boy alone</strong>, he can make up his own mind.
别管这个孩子，他会自己作决定的。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>剩下；剩余：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There were a couple of seats left at the back. 
后面还剩几个位子。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I've only got a few dollars left.
我身上只剩下几美元了。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>造成；留下 (某种结果)</strong></h4>
<p>to make sth happen or remain as a result：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>An explosion at a chemical plant has left one worker dead and four injured. 
一家化工厂爆炸造成一名工人死亡，四人受伤。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The traffic accident left her with a scar on her forehead.
那次交通事故在她的额头上留下了一个伤疤。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>留下 (便条、口信等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Someone left this note <strong>for</strong> you. / Someone left you this note.<strong>left_1</strong>
有人给你留下了这张便条。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please leave your message on the answering machine.
请在答录机上留言。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.★ <strong>遗忘；丢下：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The moment I got home, I found I had left my jacket on the playground. 
我刚到家就发现把夹克丢在操场上了。</p><footer>2008 陕西</footer></div>

<h3 id="forget-leave">辨析 forget, leave</h3>
<p><strong>forget</strong> 意为“忘记”，常用forget (about) sth,forget doing sth, “forget + that / wh- 从句” 句型。
<strong>leave</strong> 也可表示“忘记”，但常和地点状语搭配使用，意为“把 (某物) 遗留在 (某处)”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As soon as I shut the door, I realized I'd left the keys inside.
门关上的一瞬间，我意识到我把钥匙落在房间里了。</p></div>

<h4 id="7">7.★ <strong>把...交给；委托</strong></h4>
<p>to allow sb to take care of sth：</p>
<ul>
<li>leave sth with / to sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Leave your key with a neighbor in case you lock yourself out one day. 
把钥匙交给邻居吧，以防某一天你把自己锁在门外。</p><footer>2008 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Go and join in the party. Leave it to me to do the washing-up.
去参加聚会吧。我来洗碗。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="leave-behind">leave behind</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>把...丢在后面；超过：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sarah, with her long legs, soon left the rest of us behind.
萨拉腿长，很快就把我们中的其他人抛在身后。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>By opening a novel, I can leave behind my burdens and enter into a wonderful world.
打开小说，我就能放下包袱，进入一个奇妙的世界。</p><footer>2019天津改</footer></div>

<p>2.<strong>留下；忘带：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>leave new problems behind
留下新的问题</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't leave any of your belongings behind.
不要落下你的任何随身物品。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a left-behind child
留守儿童</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>永久离开：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She knew that she had left her childhood behind.
她知道童年一去不复返了。</p></div>

<h3 id="leave-off">leave off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 停止：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Barry took up the story where Justine had left off. 
巴里从贾斯廷停下的地方把故事接着讲了下去。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>不把...列入；遗漏：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We left him off the list. 
我们没把他列入名单。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A map-maker might have left the crossing off a paper map. 
也许地图的制作者在地图上遗漏了这个十字路口。</p><footer>2011 浙江</footer></div>

<h3 id="leave-out">leave out</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>遗漏；不包括：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you study in a systematic way, you won't leave anything out.
如果你用系统的方法来学习，你就不会遗漏任何东西。</p><footer>北师大⑦ - 21</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>被忽视；觉得被冷落：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>New fathers often <strong>feel left out</strong> when baby arrives. 
有了孩子后，初为人父者往往有一种被冷落的感觉。</p></div>

<h3 id="be-left-over">(be) left over</h3>
<p>1.<strong>被剩下；被留下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There were some chairs left over when everyone had sat down. 
当每个人都坐下时，还有一些椅子空着。</p><footer>2008 四川</footer></div>

<h3 id="leave-room-for">leave room for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>为…留有余地</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Now I am leaving home to college.  （2016 全国 改错）  </li>
<li>Video games can be a poor infl uence if <strong><em>_</em></strong>____ (leave) in the wrong hands.  （2015 湖南改）  </li>
<li>The teacher stressed again that the students should not leave <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ any important details while retelling the story.  （2008 湖北改）  </li>
<li>Don't leave the water <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ (run) while you brush your teeth.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. to → for  2. left  3. out  4. running  </p></div>